  "prompt": "Which are some Indian Fast-fashion Brands?",
  "response": "India has a growing fast-fashion scene, with several brands catering to the style-savvy and budget-conscious consumers. Here are some notable Indian fast-fashion brands:\n\n1. **Zara** - Although it originated in Spain, Zara has a significant presence in India and offers trendy clothing at competitive prices.\n\n2. **H&M** - Similar to Zara, H&M is a global fast-fashion retailer that operates multiple stores across India, offering a variety of trendy apparel.\n\n3. **Myntra** - An online shopping platform known for a vast selection of brands, Myntra also has its own private labels like Roadster, DressBerry, and more, focusing on the fast-fashion segment.\n\n4. **Fabindia** - While it emphasizes traditional Indian textiles and crafts, Fabindia also offers contemporary clothing that can be considered fast fashion in a local context.\n\n5. **W for Woman** - A brand offering trendy ethnic wear, W for Woman focuses on fashionable designs that cater to modern Indian women.\n\n6. **Biba** - Known for its fashionable and vibrant ethnic wear, Biba offers a wide range of clothing options that appeal to the fast-fashion market.\n\n7. **Vero Moda** - A subsidiary of the Danish fashion brand, Vero Moda has a strong presence in India, focusing on trendy women\u2019s wear.\n\n8. **Forever New** - This Australian brand has successfully captured the Indian market with its chic and trendy clothing options.\n\n9. **Ritu Kumar** - While primarily known for traditional wear, the brand has also ventured into more modern styles that fit the fast-fashion mold.\n\n10. **Pantaloons** - A part of the Aditya Birla Group, Pantaloons offers affordable and trendy clothing that appeals to a broad demographic.\n\nThese brands reflect the blend of global influences and local tastes that define the Indian fast-fashion landscape.",
